description: For sale: $239,900. Stunning 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom home located in a great neighborhood! This home has been very well cared for and updated throughout! Front entry carpet is getting a new threshold this Saturday 4/18.

Less than 10 minutes to Elk River or Big Lake. MUST SEE!

description:
For sale: $538,000. Contact the official listing agent, Julie Betzler with Realty Group for the most accurate and up-to-date information on this amazing property! Stunning new construction rambler with full unfinished basement, main level living with over 2100+ square feet on the main level alone! Future potential for nearly 4000 finished square feet in a one-story home?.WOW!  Home is built on two parcels totaling 5.07 acres, primarily level, great for future second garage or storage shed (check with county on any possible restrictions) and heavily wooded with gorgeous pines! Rural area of Big Lake yet on paved roads and easy access to Hwy 10 and conveniences in both Elk River and Big Lake!

This rambler features a large 6?x30? covered concrete front porch and steps, with maintenance free railing and recessed lighting, great for relaxing  and enjoying the outdoors. There is an attached oversized 3 car garage that is already insulated and sheetrocked with 2 insulated overhead garage doors and gas line run future heater. 

The main level features a welcoming foyer into a huge open concept great room, dining room and kitchen?you will be in awe of this space.  It truly brings the outdoors in with 4 different wood species throughout the house.  Black Ash tongue & groove covers the vaulted soaring ceilings, natural Hickory constructs the cabinetry throughout and Red Oak in natural finish is the hardwood flooring in the main living area. Cambia counters, oil rubbed bronze hardware and fixtures throughout, stainless steel kitchen appliances, recessed and flush mount light fixtures, plus ceiling fan in the great room.  There is an angled gas fireplace in the great room, perfect for those chilly nights with stone hearth and front from floor to ceiling with wood mantle.

There are also three very spacious bedrooms on the main level all with neutral carpet and upgraded padding.  The master suite has a private full bathroom with corner soaking tub looking out into the pines, separate walk-in shower tiled from floor to ceiling, tiled floors, double vanity with custom Hickory cabinets, comfort height stool and wood lined walk-in closet.  There is a also a second full bath with tile floors and Hickory vanity and linen cabinet, plus a spacious laundry room with Hickory cabinets, wash sink and ceramic tile floors. 

The lower level full basement is ready for your imagination, with an egress window for a 4th bedrooms, roughed in for a 3rd bathroom and also includes the mechanical room.

description: Recently sold: $200,500. A turn-key 2BR/2BA with beautiful backyard and the opportunity to grow. Enjoy your morning coffee or grill out in the private back patio under the shade of a custom pergola all while overlooking a beautifully landscaped yard with mature trees, a variety of perennials and raised planter beds. This property is equipped with a Nest home system, kenmore washer/dryer and a spacious two-car garage. Enjoy the convenient location to town and a great yard with this wonderful move-in ready home!

Includes 2 large bedrooms and a 3/4 bath finished with tile flooring/Faux wood and pebble accents. A large treated deck overlooks a lush irrigated green lawn and is also heavily wooded for privacy. A private trail leads to a DNR designated trout river! MN Native Landscapes prairie grass/native plants that are perfect for attracting wildlife. 15K in additional landscaping that includes raised paver patio/fire pit area, invisible fence system Newer well pressure tank/water softener, living room gas fireplace, plenty of built in storage and much more. This is home!

MAIN FLOOR FULL  BATH

Convenient to the lower level bedroom and family room.

Very large lower level bedroom with lookout windows that will make a lovely guest room or additional bedroom.

Oversized 2 car garage.  It easily accommodates two full-sized vehicles.

description: Recently sold: $296,000. Beautiful spacious rambler style home on acreage in Big Lake available now. Located across the street from the Sherburne National Wildlife Refuge and only blocks to Ann Lake. Enjoy your hobbies such as snowmobiling and fishing without the long drive up north. The inside of this home has been totally repainted with brand new carpet throughout. The kitchen has an open concept layout, with stunning hardwood floors and new appliances. The pantry is huge! There is a walk-out to an expansive 18x24 deck which would be perfect for entertaining or relaxing. The lower level is unfinished and has an abundance of space for storage or hobbies. Large windows brighten up the home. All living facilities are one one level. Private master bath. DISCLAIMER: We appreciate your interest in this rental property! Please note, there is a high volume of interest on our rental properties. The best way to schedule a showing is online. Several showings are done open house style, with multiple interested parties. This minimizes the inconvenience to our current tenants, whose time we want to remain respectful of. If after viewing the property you feel this is the perfect fit for you, please apply after verifying you meet all of our application qualifications. LEASE QUALIFICATIONS: Income: 2.5x monthly rent, determined by take-home pay. Must provide current paystubs or personal tax return. Bank Statements: No NSF history; Verifiable on-time rental payments to Landlord. Rental History: Current and previous Landlord must provide positive & verifiable rental history. If applying with other individuals, must have verifiable rental history together. Living with family is not considered verifiable rental history. Credit History: Sound financials are required. Accounts in collection, poor credit history, or late payments negatively impact application. Criminal History: No drug/violent/sexually related felonies in past 15 years. No felonies or unlawful detainers within the past 5 years. Job History: At current company a minimum of 6 months. Exceptions considered if moving from out of area to accept a job offer or promotion. Must submit Offer Letter. Pets: With owner approval and will require an additional deposit and/or fees in addition to photo(s) of pets. Check ad for property you are applying for, as some owners do NOT accept any pets. There are restrictions in place should an owner choose to allow pets: no aggressive breeds, no puppies under 12 months, no kittens. Service animals are protected by the Fair Housing Act and allowed in all properties. Requirements for a Service animal must be met or application will be denied. Applicants: Any adult over the age of 18 must apply and meet the above guidelines. The non-refundable fee is $50 per individual. If your application is denied for any reasons not listed in the criteria, you will be reimbursed your application fee. Contact us to schedule a showing.

Recently sold: $263,000. Why buy new when you can own this fully finished four bedroom, two bathroom home in Big Lake with tranquil views of the 0.27 acre lot it rests on! The adjoining eat-in kitchen includes ample cabinet/countertop space, breakfast bar--great for extra seating and stainless appliances w/gas stove! The main level also includes two bedrooms w/good sized walk-in closets and one of them w/walkthrough access to the full bathroom! The finished walkout lower level has a large family room, two bedrooms--walk-in closet in one, laundry and a ¾ bath w/built-in shelving and in-floor heat! All situated in a convenient, friendly neighborhood just minutes from outstanding schools!

Additional amenities include: patio off the family room walkout, recessed lighting, three car garage w/carriage style doors and an asphalt driveway, Finken water filtration system, drainage system and so much more!

You won?t want to miss out on the opportunity to own this well designed home for sale in Big Lake! Contact Stacy Heuer with Re/Max Results at 612-964-8469 to setup your showing today!

Easy access to HWY 10 and 25. Please set up a viewing today! Sorry, not pets.

DISCLAIMER: 
We appreciate your interest in our property! Please note, due to the high volume of interest we are not able to return every call/email to interested parties. To view the property, please schedule a showing using our online showing system. Our policy is to conduct open house showings on all properties. That way current occupants are not inconvenienced several times throughout the week. Due to this, please note that you will most likely view the property with other interested properties. If this property is the perfect fit for you, please submit your application online!

The property is not considered off-the-market until a deposit is paid, and the lease is signed by all parties. 

LEASE TERMS:
 No Pets. Service animals are protected by the Fair Housing Act and allowed in all properties.
 Net income must be 2.5x the base rent. If unable to meet this requirement, the option to pay a pro-rated amount prior to move-in is available. 
 Must be with current employer 6+ months. Exceptions are considered if moving from out of area to accept a job offer.
 Sound financials are required. History of returned payments, collection accounts, late payments and overdrafts negatively impact application.
 Must have verifiable positive rental history from current and most recent prior landlord.
 No unlawful detainers or evictions. Exceptions made if paid off in full and not within the past 5 years.
 No felony convictions within the last 10 years. Multiple felony or violent/sexual assault convictions are subject to 20 years.
 The nature, severity, and number of offenses in the last 10 years may impact approval.
 All adults 18+ must apply and meet the above guidelines
 Application fee is $50/person for credit & criminal background screening
 Lease terms are generally 12 months. We do not have our leases end during the months of October  February. Terms will be modified to reflect. If another lease term is available, it will be included in the listing.

 Contact us to schedule a showing.

description:
Recently sold: $207,000. 3BR 2BA Split Level home with attached two car garage, fenced in back yard, with many oak trees and 8? x 12? storage shed in back yard.  All appliances included, with sky lights in living room and upper bath room, to add a bright touch to the home.  
This home has a nice living room on the upper level as well as a nice family room down. Walk in closet in Master bed room, Open from main level to living room up makes for an open floor plan. Furnace is 5 years old and new water heater in 2015.  New carpet throughout house. Lots of storage area.  Located in town one block from Lake, easy access to Highway 10 and schools and play grounds are only couple blocks away. 
Big Lake is located about 35 miles northwest of Minneapolis, MN and approx. 20 East of St. Cloud, MN. on Highway #10. Monticello is located approx. 4 miles to the North. Highway #94 is 4 miles to the North as well with access to Minneapolis, MN or Fargo, ND   North Star (888) Rail is an easy 5-minute drive and offers service between Big Lake and down town Minneapolis stopping at Elk River, Ramsey, Anoka, Coon Rapids and Fridley.  Selling AS IS. Contract for Deed Available with decent down payment.  612-250-5117 cell.
